The paper presents a new optimization algorithm for deep neural networks that is both faster and more scalable than existing algorithms. The focus is on training large models, particularly for image classification tasks, which suggests a likely category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic optimization and mini-batch sizes, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is based on computing the inverse Hessian of each mini-batch, which involves numerical methods and optimization techniques that are relevant to the category of numerical analysis (cs.NE) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.NE and cs.DC.
